library(maps)
library(mapdata)
library(tidyverse)
##  Attaching packages  tidyverse 1.2.1 
##  ggplot2 3.1.0      purrr   0.2.5
##  tibble  1.4.2      dplyr   0.7.8
##  tidyr   0.8.2      stringr 1.3.1
##  readr   1.2.1      forcats 0.3.0
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
##  dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
##  dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
##  purrr::map()    masks maps::map()
EU_map <- map_data("world", region=c("Austria","Andorra","Belgium","Bulgaria","Croatia","Cyprus",
                   "Czech Rep.","Denmark","Estonia","Finland","France",
                   "Germany","Greece","Switzerland","Hungary","Italy", "Ireland", "Latvia","Liechtenstein",
                   "Lithuania","Luxembourg","Malta","Netherlands", "Norway","Poland",
                   "Portugal","Romania","Slovakia","Slovenia","Spain",
                   "Sweden", "UK"))

EU_map <- mutate(EU_map, value = NA)
EU_map[EU_map$region=="Finland",]$value <- 10
EU_map[EU_map$region=="Norway",]$value <- 10
EU_map[EU_map$region=="Spain",]$value <- 50
EU_map[EU_map$region=="Portugal",]$value <- 70
EU_map[EU_map$region=="Cyprus",]$value <- 90
head(EU_map)
##       long      lat group order  region     subregion value

ggplot() + 
  geom_polygon(data = EU_map, aes(x=long, y = lat, group = group, fill=value)) + 
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(34,71)) + 
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank()) +
  labs(x="Longitude", y="Latitude") + scale_fill_gradient(name="Antibioottiresistenssi
suhdeluku", high="red", low="darkgreen", na.value = "grey50")
